Good Afternoon Steckel Families,

This is a reminder that Tuesday June 23rd and Wednesday June 24th will be the days for drop off and pick up of student items. Second grade families will come on Tuesday and 3rd grade families will come on Wednesday. The instructions for this procedure and schedule are included in the link below and posted on Facebook. Thank you for your patience and support with this process. Please remember to wear a mask and if students are in the car they may see their teachers helping with this process so they are able to give them a wave. Thank you and have a great evening.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1NOjVCQjK1IiIxDNWGVCIqvHBAGdCVYJq7HFxtm_rt3U/edit?usp=sharing

Your Proud Principal,

Mrs. Snyder

post_text:
Updated Food Distribution Process:

Food is available for all WCSD students during the closure , regardless of free and reduced or regular pay lunch status. Meal pickups will be available at the HS parent pickup / drop off area, which is in the front of the high school nearest the pool and the gym. Pick up times will be from 10:00 - 12:00, Monday, March 23rd and Wednesday, March 25th. On Monday students will receive 2 days worth of meals and on Wednesday students will receive 3 days worth of meals. Students who need meals must be present and accompany their parents in order to receive food. Both breakfast and lunch will be provided. The food will beavailable curb-side, thus you should remain in your car to the best of your ability and food will be handed directly to you in your vehicle. The district is directing questions with regard to meals
and food pickup to Wayne Walp at (610) 782-0961 or walpw@whitehallcoplay.org.

post_text:
Good Afternoon WCSD Families,

I hope this message finds you all safe and healthy. Please be aware that at this time we do not have any new updates. We want to encourage you to work with your children at home on the extended learning activities and continue to look for new messages from their teacher. We will continue to update you with any new information from the district and/or state as we navigate this event. Please stay safe and engaged with friends and family during this difficult time. I miss you all and please continue to look on our social media pages for some future videos to stay engaged with our school community.

Mrs. Cora Snyder
Principal
Steckel Elementary School

text:
Good Afternoon WCSD Families,

I hope this message finds you all safe and healthy. Please be aware that at this time we do not have any new updates. We want to encourage you to work with your children at home on the extended learning activities and continue to look for new messages from their teacher. We will continue to update you with any new information from the district and/or state as we navigate this event. Please stay safe and engaged with friends and family during this difficult time. I miss you all and please continue to look on our social media pages for some future videos to stay engaged with our school community.

Mrs. Cora Snyder
Principal
Steckel Elementary School
Whitehall-Coplay School District
610-435-1521 ext. 1302

post_text:
Just a friendly reminder...

Food is available for all WCSD students during the closure, regardless of free and reduced or regular pay lunch status.
Meal pickups will be available each day at the HS parent pickup / drop off area, which is in the front of the high school
nearest the pool and the gym. Pick up times will be from 10:00 - 12:00, Monday-Friday. Students who need meals must be present and accompany their parents in order to receive food. Both breakfast and lunch will be provided in two
separate bags. The food will be available curb-side, thus you should remain in your car to the best of your ability and
food will be handed directly to you in your vehicle.

post_text:
Today, the President declared a National Emergency and the Governor closed all public schools in Pennsylvania for ten (10) business days. All Whitehall-Coplay School District schools will be closed from Monday, March 16, 2020, until and including, Friday, March 27, 2020. Updates will be provided as we work through this issue.
At this time, students are not required to complete any assignments.
Buildings will be accessible on Monday, March 16, 2020, from 9am -12pm for parents that need to pick up medications or other items.
All District events are canceled effective immediately.
Thank you for your cooperation and support.

post_text:
The Whitehall Coplay School District was informed that a student in the district was tested for Covid-19 as a precautionary measure. It is important to note that to our knowledge, the student has not traveled or been in contact either directly or indirectly with anyone exposed to Covid-19. We have been in communication with Local and State Health Department officials. For the safety and wellness of our students and staff, the district will be closed for cleaning today, Thursday, March 12th. Friday, March 13th schools will remain closed as this was a regularly scheduled professional development day. Regular classes will resume on Monday, March16th. It is important to reiterate that there are no known or reported cases of Covid-19 in the Whitehall Coplay School District.
We apologize for any inconveniences the late school closure may have caused. Our decisions were made in the best interest of students and staff.

Parents! MONDAY is the Steckel Fun Run. We are so close to our $10,000 goal because thus far we have raised $7,320. We cannot begin to show our gratitude for everything all the families have done for our school! Reminder if we hit our $10,000 goal Principal Snyder will have to wear a costume to school!

Weekend Challenge: The top class from 2nd and 3rd will get to PIE ALL STAR ALANNAH at the glow run!

A HUGE BONUS WEEKEND CHALLENGE: any student who gets new pledges of $1 pledge per lap donation or pledges adding up to $30 will get a Booster prize that values up to $7 pledge per lap ($210).

Get those last minute pledges in, share your students funrun.com page, and reach out the family and friends! THANK YOU for all you have done for Steckel thus far during the program.
